literally, perhaps,” he said. “You have
to draw on your life experiences to
write, I think.”

Kinder followed that reading with
other short excerpts, including a
monologue by Bill’s wife in which
Kinder told the audience to visualize
him as the character in order to
achieve the full effect.-

“Remember,” Kinder said, “I’Ve
got long blonde hair and I’m beauti-
ful.”

After the reading, a short ques-
tion—and-answer session followed. An
audience member said that he had
read that the character of Ralph was
basedon Carver.

“It’s a work of fiction,” Kinder /

responded.

The book signing was planned for
months

