crime scene, with recovery of remains con-
tinuing. But even some of the lesser-dam-
aged areas, which Evey controls, have seri-
ous problems.

In some areas, the soot damage is
intense, greasy to the touch. “It’s as if you
spray-painted everything black,” Evey said.

Even worse is the water damage.

Evey opened the door to a brand-new
Navy conference room and was greeted by
